<sect1 id="interface">
<title>Configure the Interface</title>
<para>Selecting the Interface Title button on the Preferences Dialog opens gives you access to four areas. </para>
<para>
Configure the &app; User Interface from these dialogs.
</para>
<para>
<itemizedlist>
     <listitem><para><link linkend="interface-fonts">Fonts</link></para></listitem>
     <listitem><para><link linkend="interface-html">HTML</link></para></listitem>
     <listitem><para><link linkend="interface-composer">Composer</link></para></listitem> 
     <listitem><para><link linkend="interface-miscellaneous">Miscellaneous</link></para></listitem>  
    </itemizedlist>
</para>

<sect2 id="interface-fonts">
<title>Fonts</title>
<informalexample>
<para>Settings => Preferences => Interface => Fonts
</para>
</informalexample>
</sect2>

<sect2 id="interface-html">
<title>HTML</title>
<informalexample>
<para>Settings => Preferences => Interface => HTML
</para>
</informalexample>
</sect2>

<sect2 id="interface-composer">
<title>Composer </title>
<informalexample>
<para>Settings => Preferences => Interface => Composer
</para>
</informalexample>
</sect2>

<sect2 id="interface-miscellaneous">
<title>Miscellaneous Display Items</title>

<informalexample>
<para>Settings => Preferences => Interface => Misc..
</para>
</informalexample>
<para>Set the window manager format</para>
</sect2>
</sect1>
